<P>&nbsp;</P>
</FONT><B><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=4><P>The Quadratic Formula</P></B></FONT>
<FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=2>

<P>If the expression ax<SUP>2 </SUP>+ bx + c <B>cannot</B> be easily <B>factorised</B> we use the so-called <B>Quadratic Formula</B>.   Work through <a href="runcal.htm#==k:\calmat\tcrun.exe calpopup //?~ 0 1 30 e 0~?">1-30 section e</a>.   Examples are solved using the Quadratic Formula on pages 4 and 5 of your lecture notes.   Try <a href="launch.htm#q0648">q0648</a>.</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"></P>

<P>&nbsp;</P>
